        <h1>Payson Seminary</h1>

        <p>The Payson Seminary represents one of Northway Construction's most significant educational projects—a complete ground-up construction of a 12,000 square foot seminary building designed to serve Payson High School students for generations. This substantial project demonstrates our ability to handle major new construction from site development through final finishes.</p>

        <p>The building includes multiple classrooms designed for interactive religious education, faculty areas and offices supporting teaching staff, comfortable common areas for student gathering and socialization, modern restrooms serving daily building occupancy, and complete site development including parking, landscaping, and utilities. Every element was coordinated to create a welcoming, functional educational environment.</p>

        <p>Ground-up construction on this scale requires managing numerous trades, maintaining strict quality control, and meeting demanding schedules to ensure availability for the start of the school year. We delivered a building that will serve Payson's religious education needs for decades while meeting all modern building codes and accessibility standards.</p>

        <h3>Project Highlights</h3>
        <ul style="line-height: 2; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <li>12,000 SF ground-up seminary construction</li>
          <li>Multiple classrooms with modern educational features</li>
          <li>Faculty offices and support spaces</li>
          <li>Student common areas and gathering spaces</li>
          <li>Complete site development including parking and utilities</li>
          <li>On-schedule delivery for start of school year</li>
        </ul>

        <p>The Payson Seminary stands as a testament to Northway Construction's capability to deliver major educational facilities that serve Utah communities with excellence and lasting quality.</p>
